			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">OK, this is a pretty elementary question, but was looking to see if anyone had any advice. Having played several other casters at the highest levels, I have become accustomed to walking that fine aggro line when killing high-level mobs.  With a wiard, chanter or necro, you have a combination of abilities that allows you to survive putting a toe over the aggro line and getting summoned.  Whether it is FD, Rune, or Jolt, as long as you don't go crazy and get the mob locked on to you, you are generally fine to e patient and let the tank regain control.
<br />

<br />
Am I missing any similar type of ability as a mage, or is it simply that we need to be much more careful about approaching that line?  At level 59, getting called to the front of the line by a POS or BOT Giant is a death sentence.  Should we simply work on AC and HP to the point that we can generally walk away from that first round, and be as careful as possible about NOT getting summoned?
<br />

<br />
Just curious if I am being dense and missing any good aggro managment/survival tactics while doing large mobs in a group.
<br />

<br />
Ledorus Nolitari
<br />
Level 59 Conjurer
<br />
Quellious Server</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
