				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Thanks for all the help!  I will do my best to get the shield, but I think that might be a ways off for me.  Not sure my guild can handle the Arch-Lich yet.  Something nice to set my sights on though!
<br />

<br />
A couple of words off topic to the person who mentioned boggle.  There is very little you can do if your tank just isn't doing his job and holding aggro.  If, however, I get stuck with a tank that isn't maintaining aggro and Tash is required, I generally use Tash, then Boggle, then Slow.  I find that most of the time, boggle will land after mobs are Tashed, and even if not It never really generates any additional aggro when it is cast, so at least you have spaced out the huge aggro hits from Tash and slow by a few more seconds.  Just my two cents.
<br />

<br />
Thanks again for all the advice!
<br />

