			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I didn't say SCS wasn't wonderful; it is.  I've just not had that much problems with agro as others here have.  I chain Sun Vortex from around 99% (unless the raid has uber DPS and the mob is getting beat down fast) and can only count one mob where I was summoned, and it was at 3% (/rude Vindi).
<br />

<br />
I also never have mana problems, but that can be contributed to other things.  In a BoT exp group, I'm usually chaining FBoT/Sun Vortex or Black Steel.  I usually stick to FBoT/Sun Vortex in HoH/Tactics and I never have any agro problems.  Alot depends on your group's tank, which is why those restricted zones (e.g. Tactics) are great to group in.  You get good tanks most of those times.
<br />

<br />
