				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">No, not a lie, a bit naïve maybe or even ignorant. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Anyway, I don't have aggro issues in a lot of other places either, so what it probabky boils down to is how well your MT holds hate.
<br />

<br />
Pet helps as well, discussed somewhere else.
<br />

<br />
If your MT has a way to hold hate good enough, You don't need special aggro management.
<br />

<br />
Eventually, maybe, most mages will have, in their guild, a Warrior (MT) with .. let's say a BoW (Drops form RZtW). That warrior can then hold aggro better than he could before, which means you can nuke more when he tanks. There are other weapons out there generating hate as well.
<br />

<br />
Test your limits, you will die finding them, but once found you will probably be a better mage.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
